11:08.201 --> 11:10.602
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE OTHER RAPE VICTIM

11:10.604 --> 11:12.037
THAT LEE TOLD US ABOUT?

11:12.039 --> 11:13.605
UH, SHE CAME OUT
FOR THE TRIAL,

11:13.607 --> 11:15.173
BUT THE JUDGE
WOULDN'T LET HER TESTIFY.

11:15.175 --> 11:18.109
CORPORAL LAURA DAY.

11:18.111 --> 11:19.678
SHE'S STILL IN LOS ANGELES.

11:19.680 --> 11:23.348
AND SHE LIVES LESS THAN A MILE
FROM OUR MURDER SCENE.

11:32.024 --> 11:35.894
HYDROXYZINE IS A FAIRLY MILD
ANTIANXIETY MEDICATION,

11:35.896 --> 11:37.896
BUT I CANNOT BELIEVE
THAT THIS IS PART

11:37.898 --> 11:39.798
OF SHARON BECK'S TREATMENT
IN REHAB.

11:39.800 --> 11:41.566
AM I WRONG?
NO.

11:41.568 --> 11:44.202
HYDROXYZINE ALSO COVERS UP
THE SIDE EFFECTS OF HEROIN,

11:44.204 --> 11:46.705
AND IT'S A CHEAP WAY
TO BUMP UP YOUR HIGH.

11:46.707 --> 11:49.541
SO RUSTY'S MOM
IS PLANNING ON USING AGAIN?

11:49.543 --> 11:51.042
WELL, WHERE SHE IS?

11:51.044 --> 11:52.711
WALL-TO-WALL ADDICTS
JONESING UNDER A COURT ORDER --

11:52.713 --> 11:55.246
BEST PLACE IN THE WORLD
TO SCORE DRUGS.

11:55.248 --> 11:56.915
IF HIS MOM BROKE THE LAW,
PROBLEM SOLVED.

11:56.917 --> 11:58.216
YOU COULD PUT HER
IN JAIL.

11:58.218 --> 11:59.718
THAT'S NOT MY GOAL.

11:59.720 --> 12:04.089
MOST ADDICTS' STRONG SUIT --
MANIPULATION OF FAMILY.

12:05.758 --> 12:08.393
JACKIE CHAIDEZ
JUST CALLED ME IN TEARS.

12:08.395 --> 12:09.594
SORRY, CAPTAIN.

12:09.596 --> 12:11.162
IT WAS EITHER LET HIM IN
OR SHOOT HIM.

12:11.164 --> 12:12.664
FIRST YOU DRAG HER
DOWN HERE.

12:12.666 --> 12:14.265
THEN YOU SEND S.I.D.
TO PRINT HER HOUSE AND CAR?

12:14.267 --> 12:16.568
IS THAT YOUR IDEA
OF ADVOCATING FOR THE VICTIM?

12:16.570 --> 12:19.237
MR. LEE, I HAVE A VICTIM, TOO,
AND I DON'T <i>ADVOCATE.</i>

12:19.239 --> 12:20.839
I <i>INVESTIGATE.</i>

12:20.841 --> 12:24.509
THEN INVESTIGATE THIS --
LUCAS CROSS WAS 6'3",

12:24.511 --> 12:27.846
220 POUNDS,
TWICE AS HEAVY AS JACKIE.

12:27.848 --> 12:30.515
YOU SEEM <i>REALLY</i> FAMILIAR
WITH JACKIE'S MEASUREMENTS.

12:30.517 --> 12:33.251
BUT WHAT ABOUT CROSS'S
OTHER RAPE VICTIM --

12:33.253 --> 12:34.753
CORPORAL LAURA DAY?

12:34.755 --> 12:37.288
CAN YOU DESCRIBE
HER PHYSIQUE, TOO?

12:37.290 --> 12:40.191
CORPORAL DAY'S NOT RELEVANT.
AND SHE LIVES IN ILLINOIS.

12:40.193 --> 12:43.928
ACTUALLY, SHE HAS AN APARTMENT
A HALF A MILE FROM MR. CROSS --

12:43.930 --> 12:45.396
BECAUSE SHE NEVER LEFT.

12:45.398 --> 12:48.366
WE REALLY APPRECIATE
YOUR CONCERN,

12:48.368 --> 12:50.268
BUT WHY DON'T YOU DO US ALL
A FAVOR

12:50.270 --> 12:52.237
AND DON'T CONTACT
ANY MORE OF OUR SUSPECTS

12:52.239 --> 12:54.439
BEFORE WE TALK TO THEM.

12:54.441 --> 12:58.476
I'LL CONTACT WHOEVER I WANT
BECAUSE I'M IN THE BUSINESS
OF PROTECTING THE PUBLIC.

12:58.478 --> 13:00.345
WHAT BUSINESS ARE YOU IN?

13:06.652 --> 13:10.955
MR. LEE'S CONSCIENCE
APPEARS...OVERFULL.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.324
WELL, HE'S RIGHT
ABOUT ONE THING.

13:13.326 --> 13:14.626
THE CRIME SCENE DOES MAKE
THE KILLER LOOK MORE LIKE A MAN

13:14.628 --> 13:16.394
THAN A WOMAN.

13:16.396 --> 13:20.431
BUT IF THAT WOMAN HAD PEPPER
SPRAY AND A MILITARY BACKGROUND,

13:20.433 --> 13:22.367
IT COULD MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

13:25.905 --> 13:29.741
YOU CAME OUT TO LOS ANGELES
TO TESTIFY AGAINST LUCAS CROSS?

13:29.743 --> 13:31.209
CHECK.

13:33.245 --> 13:36.347
WHY DID YOU STAY HERE
AFTER THE TRIAL WAS OVER?

13:36.349 --> 13:38.983
I'D SPENT PRACTICALLY ALL
OF MY MONEY DRIVING OUT HERE

13:38.985 --> 13:41.753
BECAUSE I AM,
AS THEY SAY,

13:41.755 --> 13:43.955
<i>BETWEEN OPPORTUNITIES.</i>

13:43.957 --> 13:46.858
SHE WOULD ALSO APPEAR TO BE
BETWEEN DRINKS.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.193
<i>LOOK, MY CRAPPY CAR</i>

13:48.195 --> 13:50.595
COULDN'T MAKE IT ALL THE WAY
BACK TO CHICAGO.

13:50.597 --> 13:52.597
MA'AM, HOW DID YOU HAPPEN
TO CHOOSE THE LOCATION

13:52.599 --> 13:54.332
OF THE APARTMENT
YOU MOVED INTO OUT HERE?

13:54.334 --> 13:57.602
CHEAP...RENT.

13:57.604 --> 13:59.470
SLIGHTLY HOSTILE.

13:59.472 --> 14:01.372
OR HIGH.

14:01.374 --> 14:03.341
YOU WANT ME
TO STOP THIS?
NOT YET.

14:03.343 --> 14:04.876
Sykes: <i>DID YOU KNOW</i>
<i>LUCAS CROSS LIVED</i>

14:04.878 --> 14:06.344
<i>IN EASY WALKING DISTANCE</i>
<i>FROM YOU?</i>

14:06.346 --> 14:08.880
<i>WELL [CHUCKLES]</i>
<i>NOT ANYMORE.</i>

14:08.882 --> 14:10.949
[ CHUCKLES ]
I SAW ON THE NEWS LAST NIGHT

14:10.951 --> 14:13.051
WHERE SOMEBODY
TOOK A KNIFE TO HIM.

14:13.053 --> 14:18.089
COULD WE ASK YOU ABOUT
YOUR RELATIONSHIP TO LUCAS?

14:19.358 --> 14:21.559
MY RELATIONSHIP.

14:22.895 --> 14:25.063
DID HE REALLY
JUST SAY THAT?

14:25.065 --> 14:27.198
OKAY, BUZZ, HOLD ON.
NONE OF THIS IS USABLE.

14:27.200 --> 14:29.534
<i>YOU WANT TO ASK ME</i>
<i>ABOUT THE PARTICULARS</i>

14:29.536 --> 14:31.970
<i>OF MY RELATIONSHIP</i>
<i>WITH MY RAPIST?!</i>
<i>NO, NO, NO, NO.</i>
<i>DON'T TURN IT OFF YET.</i>

14:31.972 --> 14:34.539
IT MAY BE UNUSABLE,
BUT I'M FASCINATED.

14:34.541 --> 14:36.040
<i>I THINK</i>
<i>YOU MISUNDERSTAND.</i>
<i>OH.</i>

14:36.042 --> 14:37.642
<i>WHEN WE USE THE WORD</i>
<i>"RELATIONSHIP,"</i>

14:37.644 --> 14:39.544
WE MEAN CONNECTIONS
AT THEIR MOST BASIC LEVEL...

14:39.546 --> 14:41.379
MM.
...THE INS AND OUTS

14:41.381 --> 14:43.648
OF HOW YOU AND LUCAS CROSS
KNEW EACH OTHER

14:43.650 --> 14:46.384
AND HOW YOU BECAME, FOR LACK
OF A BETTER WORD, HIS VICTIM.
[ SIGHS ]

14:46.386 --> 14:48.253
DETECTIVE SYKES.

14:48.255 --> 14:50.555
YEAH.

14:50.557 --> 14:55.093
NO ONE GAVE A DAMN
WHAT LUCAS DID TO ME

14:55.095 --> 14:58.396
UNTIL SOMEBODY KILLED HIM,
NOT THE ARMY, NOT HIS EMPLOYERS,

14:58.398 --> 15:01.065
NOT THE POLICE,
NOT EVEN MY FAMILY!

15:01.067 --> 15:03.501
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT
MY RELATIONSHIP?!

15:03.503 --> 15:05.737
WE CAN'T USE ANYTHING SHE SAYS
WHEN SHE'S DRUNK.

15:05.739 --> 15:07.772
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE HER OUT
FOR A CUP OF COFFEE,

15:07.774 --> 15:10.909
GET HER CALM, SOBER HER UP,
GAIN HER CONFIDENCE IF YOU CAN.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.744
GREAT IDEA.
I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT.

15:12.746 --> 15:15.947
OKAY. YEAH.

15:15.949 --> 15:19.250
[ INDISTINCT SINGING
OVER RADIO ]

15:19.252 --> 15:22.587
SORRY I GOT SO INTENSE
BACK THERE.

15:22.589 --> 15:24.856
I JUST -- [ LAUGHS ]

15:24.858 --> 15:28.760
I CANNOT BELIEVE HOW YOU GUYS,
LIKE, DISMISSED ME

15:28.762 --> 15:29.694
UNTIL LUCAS DIED.

15:29.696 --> 15:31.129
[ SCOFFS ]

15:31.131 --> 15:34.599
CAN I ASK YOU A PERSONAL
QUESTION, OFF THE RECORD?

15:34.601 --> 15:39.137
ARE YOU DRUNK OR HIGH
OR BOTH?

15:40.706 --> 15:44.142
IF I DID DRUGS,
I'D BE DEAD BY NOW.

15:44.144 --> 15:45.944
YOU DRINK A LOT?

15:45.946 --> 15:48.212
ONLY AS MUCH AS I CAN.

15:49.715 --> 15:51.616
DO YOU KNOW KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?

15:51.618 --> 15:52.717
WHAT?

15:52.719 --> 15:55.653
I SURRENDER.

15:55.655 --> 15:57.822
I WON'T MAKE YOU ASK ME
THE PLAY-BY-PLAY.

15:57.824 --> 15:59.657
I'LL GIVE YOU
THE WHOLE SOB STORY

15:59.659 --> 16:02.427
ON MY RELATIONSHIP
WITH LUCAS CROSS.

16:02.429 --> 16:03.995
JUST DON'T EXPECT TEARS.

16:03.997 --> 16:05.496
OKAY.

16:05.498 --> 16:07.799
YOU KNOW WHAT IT FEELS LIKE
TO BE SURROUNDED

16:07.801 --> 16:11.402
BY A BUNCH OF HORNY,
LONELY, ARMED MEN

16:11.404 --> 16:14.472
IN A FOREIGN COUNTRY
24 HOURS A DAY?

16:14.474 --> 16:16.975
I WAS AN M.P.
WITH THE 101st,

16:16.977 --> 16:20.778
STATIONED AT AN F.O.B.
OUT OF BAGRAM IN '08,

16:20.780 --> 16:22.513
AND IN KABUL, TOO.

16:23.749 --> 16:25.850
I KNOW.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.854
MM.

16:29.856 --> 16:33.491
WELL, LUCAS WAS A, UH --
A PRIVATE CONTRACTOR,

16:33.493 --> 16:36.027
LIKE A CATERER
FOR EMBASSY TYPES.

16:36.029 --> 16:38.363
AND IT SEEMED RUDE

16:38.365 --> 16:42.333
TO ALWAYS TAKE HIS FOOD
AND AVOID HIS COMPANY.

16:42.335 --> 16:47.005
ON THE SECOND DATE,
WE...ENDED UP IN HIS TRAILER.

16:47.007 --> 16:49.640
CONTRACTORS
HAD PRIVATE QUARTERS.

16:49.642 --> 16:51.476
RIGHT.

16:51.478 --> 16:53.845
HE PUTS ON
SOME LOUD MUSIC,

16:53.847 --> 16:57.548
STARTS PAWING ME
BEFORE I CAN EVEN SIT DOWN.

16:57.550 --> 17:00.785
I GO TO LEAVE.
THE DOOR IS LOCKED.

17:00.787 --> 17:02.787
HE, UH...

17:04.957 --> 17:06.624
HE PINS ME DOWN.

17:06.626 --> 17:09.694
HE PUTS A KNIFE
TO MY THROAT.

17:09.696 --> 17:13.431
AND HE RAPES ME.

17:15.134 --> 17:19.537
I REMEMBER HIS BREATH...

17:19.539 --> 17:22.840
AND HIS HANDS...

17:22.842 --> 17:26.210
[INHALES SHARPLY]
AND HIM SAYING OVER AND OVER,

17:26.212 --> 17:29.080
"YOU LIKE IT ROUGH,
DON'T YOU, BITCH?"

17:31.517 --> 17:33.651
AND AFTERWARD,
YOU FILED CHARGES?

17:33.653 --> 17:36.387
AND YOUR FELLOW M.P.s
QUESTIONED HIM.

17:36.389 --> 17:39.991
OF COURSE,
LUCAS DENIED EVERYTHING.

17:39.993 --> 17:41.926
NEXT THING I KNEW,

17:41.928 --> 17:45.430
HIS COMPANY PUNISHED HIM
WITH A TRANSFER HOME,

17:45.432 --> 17:48.099
AND I JUST
HAD TO LIVE WITH IT.

17:51.270 --> 17:53.404
DO YOU HAVE A BOYFRIEND?

17:53.406 --> 17:55.440
I'M SEEING THIS GUY.

17:56.909 --> 17:59.043
YES.
YES.

17:59.045 --> 18:01.913
I HAVE A BOYFRIEND, YES.

18:01.915 --> 18:06.117
AND WHEN HE TOUCHES YOU,
HOW DOES IT MAKE YOU FEEL?

18:06.119 --> 18:09.454
DO YOU WANT TO SCREAM?

18:09.456 --> 18:11.856
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT
I WANT TO DO

18:11.858 --> 18:14.459
EVERY TIME
A GUY EVEN LOOKS AT ME.

18:16.628 --> 18:22.533
SO...IMAGINE HOW I FELT
LAST YEAR,

18:22.535 --> 18:26.104
WHEN LUCAS POKED ME
ON FACEBOOK.

18:26.106 --> 18:29.040
HE ASKED ME TO FRIEND HIM,

18:29.042 --> 18:32.210
LIKE IN HIS LIZARD BRAIN,
WE HAD ACTUALLY DATED.

18:32.212 --> 18:36.047
"HEY, BABE, IF YOU'RE EVER
IN CALIFORNIA, HIT ME UP."

18:36.049 --> 18:39.584
"HIT...ME...UP."

18:39.586 --> 18:40.885
OH, GOD.

18:40.887 --> 18:42.286
SO...

18:42.288 --> 18:43.888
[ SCOFFS ]
...WHEN THE PROSECUTOR --

18:43.890 --> 18:46.124
DDA LEE --
WHEN HE REACHED OUT

18:46.126 --> 18:47.992
AND ASKED YOU TO TESTIFY
IN JACKIE'S CASE --

18:47.994 --> 18:49.961
OH, I WAS THRILLED.

18:49.963 --> 18:53.965
I-I QUIT MY CRAPPY JOB
AND I PACKED MY CRAPPY CAR

18:53.967 --> 18:56.267
AND I DROVE
CLEAR ACROSS THE COUNTRY

18:56.269 --> 18:58.302
JUST SO
I COULD TAKE THE STAND.

18:58.304 --> 19:01.572
BUT...
THE JUDGE WOULDN'T LET ME

19:01.574 --> 19:04.742
BECAUSE I WAS THE BITCH
WHO LIKED IT ROUGH.

19:04.744 --> 19:06.677
THAT'S NOT WHY
YOU WEREN'T HEARD.

19:06.679 --> 19:08.746
AND LOOK,
YOU NEVER HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT

19:08.748 --> 19:10.781
THE HORRIBLE STUFF
LUCAS SAID ABOUT YOU

19:10.783 --> 19:12.583
BECAUSE
HE CAN NEVER SAY IT AGAIN.

19:12.585 --> 19:15.453
I KNOW.

19:15.455 --> 19:16.854
IT'S KIND OF HARD TO TALK

19:16.856 --> 19:19.023
WHEN YOUR THROAT IS CUT,
ISN'T IT?

19:20.592 --> 19:22.994
HOW DID YOU KNOW
HIS THROAT WAS CUT?

19:22.996 --> 19:25.596
'CAUSE, SEE, I-I WAS --
I WAS -- I WAS REALLY DRUNK

19:25.598 --> 19:27.331
WHEN I LEFT LUCAS'
LAST NIGHT,

19:27.333 --> 19:29.767
AND HE WAS STILL YOU KNOW
[GURGLES] GURGLING,

19:29.769 --> 19:34.005
JUST SQUIRTING BLOOD EVERYWHERE
[Laughing] SO I KNOW --

19:34.007 --> 19:36.007
I KNOW
THAT HE CAN'T TALK,

19:36.009 --> 19:38.176
AND I HAVE BEEN CELEBRATING
ALL DAY.

19:38.178 --> 19:40.011
OH, MY GOD.
LAURA, PLEASE. YOU DIDN'T.

19:40.013 --> 19:41.846
I DID.

19:41.848 --> 19:43.347
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

19:43.349 --> 19:46.017
I KILLED
THAT SON OF A BITCH.

19:50.522 --> 19:53.724
[ LAUGHS ]

20:02.901 --> 20:06.537
I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW MANY TIMES
PEOPLE SAY, "HEY, I DID IT,"

20:06.539 --> 20:08.739
AND THEN
YOU GUYS CAN'T ARREST THEM.

20:08.741 --> 20:10.408
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT'S WRONG THIS TIME?

20:10.410 --> 20:12.710
DID SHE END THE SENTENCE
WITH A PREPOSITION OR SOMETHING?

20:12.712 --> 20:14.478
SHE WASN'T MIRANDIZED,

20:14.480 --> 20:16.581
HER CONFESSION WASN'T RECORDED,
AND SHE WAS DRUNK.

20:16.583 --> 20:18.316
MM.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

20:19.918 --> 20:21.919
SPEAKING OF DRUNKS.

20:22.754 --> 20:24.055
HI, MOM.

20:24.057 --> 20:25.856
GOOD MORNING, SUNSHINE.

20:25.858 --> 20:27.825
ARE YOU STILL COMING TO HELP ME
MOVE OUT OF REHAB TONIGHT?

20:27.827 --> 20:29.260
UH-HUH.
I'm grateful to be here,

20:29.262 --> 20:32.597
But, oh, my God,
I cannot wait to get out!

20:32.599 --> 20:35.199
EVERYTHING IS SUPPOSED TO BE
BETTER AT THE HALFWAY HOUSE,

20:35.201 --> 20:36.567
INCLUDING THE COFFEE.

20:36.569 --> 20:38.402
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:38.404 --> 20:41.105
UM...

20:41.107 --> 20:43.941
DID YOU FILL
MY PRESCRIPTION?

20:43.943 --> 20:45.343
I'M ON IT. YEAH.

20:45.345 --> 20:47.011
Oh, thank you.

20:47.013 --> 20:48.746
AND REMEMBER --
BRING ME THE RECEIPT.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.581
I have to keep track.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.750
I WILL.

20:52.752 --> 20:55.853
UM, OKAY,
I-I'M GONNA GO.

20:55.855 --> 20:57.722
UM, I'LL --
I'LL GET OVER THERE

20:57.724 --> 20:59.523
AS SOON AS I CAN
AFTER SCHOOL.

20:59.525 --> 21:01.859
All right. Thank you, honey.
I love you.

21:01.861 --> 21:04.095
I LOVE YOU.

21:04.097 --> 21:05.963
I'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.

21:09.935 --> 21:11.702
[ SNIFFLES ]

21:14.473 --> 21:20.111
THAT PRESCRIPTION THAT MY MOM
GAVE ME TO BE FILLED --

21:20.113 --> 21:22.747
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG WITH IT,
ISN'T THERE?

21:22.749 --> 21:24.148
YES.

21:24.150 --> 21:27.485
DID IT EVEN COME
FROM THE REHAB?

21:27.487 --> 21:32.123
NO.
IT WAS A FORGERY.

21:32.125 --> 21:34.425
AND THE DRUG
ISN'T SOMETHING

21:34.427 --> 21:36.827
THAT ADDICTS
SHOULD BE TAKING AT ALL.

21:36.829 --> 21:39.463
HOW DID SHE EXPECT
TO GET AWAY WITH THIS?

21:39.465 --> 21:41.899
I WON'T PRETEND THAT THIS IS
ANYTHING BUT DISAPPOINTING,

21:41.901 --> 21:45.403
BUT YOU HAVE CHOICES HERE,
AND ONE IS TO TALK TO HER.

21:45.405 --> 21:47.805
IF YOU WANT, I COULD GO WITH YOU
AND WAIT OUTSIDE.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.740
NO. NO.
I DO NOT WANT YOU THERE.

21:51.476 --> 21:53.077
I'M -- I'M SORRY.

21:53.079 --> 21:56.013
UM, WHAT I --
WHAT I MEAN IS THAT...

21:56.015 --> 21:58.349
I WOULD RATHER HANDLE THIS ONE
ON MY OWN.

21:58.351 --> 21:59.750
I UNDERSTAND.

22:01.820 --> 22:05.289
IT COULD BE THAT CONFRONTING
YOUR MOTHER WITH THE TRUTH

22:05.291 --> 22:08.259
MIGHT MAKE HER RETHINK
WHAT SHE'S DOING.

22:08.261 --> 22:10.094
THE TRUTH.

22:10.096 --> 22:13.497
I DON'T KNOW IF SHE'S EVER SAID
ONE TRUE THING TO ME

22:13.499 --> 22:15.199
IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

22:16.835 --> 22:19.970
Sanchez: WELL, WHATEVER OTHER
LIES SHE MAY HAVE TOLD,

22:19.972 --> 22:22.940
LAURA DAY LOVES CRAFT BEER.

22:22.942 --> 22:24.508
WE FOUND A LOT OF EMPTIES

22:24.510 --> 22:26.677
IN CORPORAL DAY'S APARTMENT
AND IN HER VEHICLE.

22:26.679 --> 22:29.513
Flynn: MM. NICE CAR, TOO.
LATE MODEL.

22:29.515 --> 22:31.315
SHE LIED ABOUT THAT.
AND HER HOME?

22:31.317 --> 22:33.851
WELL, THAT'S ANOTHER LIE.
IT'S NOT LOW-RENT.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.353
IT'S A PRETTY CUSH APARTMENT.

22:35.355 --> 22:36.887
IT'S GOT A WASHER/DRYER,
DISHWASHER.

22:36.889 --> 22:38.055
Sanchez:
HERE'S WHAT WE DIDN'T FIND --

22:38.057 --> 22:40.191
BLOOD, PEPPER SPRAY,
OR A KNIFE.

22:40.193 --> 22:43.194
HMM. SO, THIS WOMAN
ADMITTED TO MURDER.

22:43.196 --> 22:45.363
WHY IS SHE LYING ABOUT
ALL THESE OTHER LITTLE THINGS?

22:45.365 --> 22:47.198
SHE DIDN'T LIE
ABOUT BEING SEXUALLY ASSAULTED

22:47.200 --> 22:49.734
WHILE SERVING OUR COUNTRY
IN UNIFORM.

22:49.736 --> 22:51.702
THAT HAPPENED,
LIEUTENANT.

22:51.704 --> 22:53.637
AND LIKE A LOT
OF OTHER UGLY TRUTHS,

22:53.639 --> 22:55.206
IT GOT SWEPT
UNDER THE RUG.

22:55.208 --> 22:57.041
SHE ONLY CONFESSED

22:57.043 --> 23:00.244
BECAUSE SOMEONE
WAS FINALLY LISTENING TO HER.

23:01.913 --> 23:04.048
I'M SORRY
I DIDN'T SEE IT COMING,

23:04.050 --> 23:06.717
AND IT WAS A MISTAKE
NOT TO RECORD IT.

23:06.719 --> 23:10.054
IF GETTING A CONFESSION
FROM A SUSPECT IS A MISTAKE,

23:10.056 --> 23:11.756
LET'S MAKE MORE MISTAKES.

23:13.892 --> 23:15.426
LOOK,
SHE ALREADY SAID IT ONCE.

23:15.428 --> 23:17.862
ALL WE NEED FOR HER TO DO
IS TO SAY IT AGAIN,

23:17.864 --> 23:19.930
THIS TIME SOBER.

23:22.734 --> 23:24.435
IF YOU CANNOT AFFORD
AN ATTORNEY,

23:24.437 --> 23:26.170
ONE WILL BE APPOINTED TO YOU
BY THE STATE.

23:26.172 --> 23:27.772
<i>HAVE YOU HEARD</i>
<i>AND UNDERSTOOD THESE RIGHTS</i>

23:27.774 --> 23:29.407
<i>AS THEY HAVE BEEN READ</i>
<i>TO YOU?</i>

23:29.409 --> 23:31.242
<i>YEAH.</i>
<i>YOU PUT AMY IN THERE?</i>

23:31.244 --> 23:33.110
THEY HAVE A RELATIONSHIP.

23:33.112 --> 23:36.414
I'M HOPEFUL SHE'LL GET HER
TO CONFESS AGAIN.

23:36.416 --> 23:38.115
THIS TIME ON CAMERA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:38.117 --> 23:40.384
WE DIDN'T RECORD ANYTHING
IN THE GOOD OLD DAYS

23:40.386 --> 23:41.786
AND STILL MADE OUR CASES.

23:41.788 --> 23:44.255
BUT NOW THAT THE DINOSAURS
ARE EXTINCT...

23:44.257 --> 23:46.357
CAN'T YOU JUST FIRE HIM?

23:46.359 --> 23:49.093
ANY IDIOT CAN HIT "RECORD."

23:49.095 --> 23:50.928
BE MY GUEST.
<i>I JUST NEED TO GO OVER</i>
<i>EVERYTHING YOU SAID,</i>

23:50.930 --> 23:52.897
HAVE YOU WRITE SOME OF IT DOWN
SO WE CAN --

23:52.899 --> 23:55.099
I SAID I DID IT.
I KILLED LUCAS CROSS.

23:55.101 --> 23:57.435
WHAT ELSE
DO YOU NEED ME TO DO? GOD.

23:57.437 --> 23:58.936
HOW DID YOU GET
INTO HIS APARTMENT?

23:58.938 --> 24:02.106
THROUGH THE SLIDING GLASS DOOR
IN THE BACK.

24:02.108 --> 24:04.975
<i>THERE'S A LITTLE PATIO</i>
<i>BEHIND THE BUILDING</i>

24:04.977 --> 24:06.444
<i>WITH A PRIVACY FENCE.</i>

24:06.446 --> 24:08.446
<i>LUCAS LEFT</i>
<i>THE SLIDER UNLOCKED.</i>

24:08.448 --> 24:10.448
<i>HE LIKED TO GO OUT THERE</i>
<i>AND SMOKE.</i>

24:10.450 --> 24:13.551
SO FAR, EVERYTHING SHE SAYS
MATCHES THE VIDEO.
THANK YOU, BUZZ.

24:13.553 --> 24:16.754
<i>I LET MYSELF IN,</i>
<i>HID IN THE CLOSET, WAITED.</i>

24:16.756 --> 24:18.122
WHICH CLOSET?

24:18.124 --> 24:19.457
<i>WHICH CLOSET?</i>

24:19.459 --> 24:21.125
<i>WHICH ROOM?</i>

24:21.127 --> 24:23.160
<i>TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,</i>
<i>I WAS A LITTLE DRUNK.</i>

24:23.162 --> 24:26.831
SOBER ENOUGH
NOT TO LEAVE ANY PRINTS.

24:26.833 --> 24:28.165
<i>I USED GLOVES.</i>

24:28.167 --> 24:30.801
THERE WAS ALSO NO BLOOD,
LAURA.

24:30.803 --> 24:34.171
<i>WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?</i>
<i>THERE WAS BLOOD EVERYWHERE.</i>

24:34.173 --> 24:36.073
<i>NOT IN YOUR APARTMENT</i>
<i>OR YOUR CAR</i>

24:36.075 --> 24:37.641
<i>OR ON ANY</i>
<i>OF YOUR CLOTHING.</i>

24:37.643 --> 24:40.845
<i>OH, MY GOD.</i>
<i>YOU THINK I'M MAKING THIS UP?</i>

24:40.847 --> 24:43.080
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?
LUCAS CAME HOME.

24:43.082 --> 24:44.915
I JUMPED OUT OF THE CLOSET
WITH A BIG FREAKING KNIFE,

24:44.917 --> 24:47.318
AND I CUT HIS THROAT.

24:47.320 --> 24:49.753
<i>HOW MANY TIMES</i>
<i>DID YOU STAB HIM?</i>
<i>WHAT DIFFERENCE</i>
<i>DOES THAT MAKE?</i>

24:49.755 --> 24:52.356
WE GOT HER.
<i>SHE</i> GOT HER.

24:52.358 --> 24:53.824
OKAY. GOOD CALL.

24:53.826 --> 24:55.259
WHICH HAND WAS THE KNIFE IN

24:55.261 --> 24:57.161
WHEN YOU SUPPOSEDLY CUT
HIS THROAT?

24:57.163 --> 24:59.430
I TOLD YOU I WAS DRUNK.
WHICH HAND?

24:59.432 --> 25:02.266
WHEN YOU WRITE IT ALL DOWN,
YOU HAVE TO BE SPECIFIC.

25:02.268 --> 25:03.834
DETAILS.

25:03.836 --> 25:06.270
LOOK, I AM TIRED.

25:06.272 --> 25:07.872
SO GO GET ME
SOMETHING TO DRINK

25:07.874 --> 25:09.874
AND POLISH A MEDAL
FOR SOLVING YOUR CASE,

25:09.876 --> 25:13.077
BUT I AM DONE TRYING TO PROVE
THAT I WAS THERE.

25:18.950 --> 25:20.551
MUSIC.

25:22.187 --> 25:23.721
WHAT ABOUT MUSIC?

25:23.723 --> 25:26.524
I TURNED IT UP TO COVER
THE SOUND OF THE STRUGGLE...

25:26.526 --> 25:30.361
LIKE HE DID TO ME.

25:30.363 --> 25:33.397
YEAH.

25:35.534 --> 25:36.967
[ SIGHS ]

25:36.969 --> 25:38.235
I WANT YOU
AT THE PRESS CONFERENCE.

25:38.237 --> 25:40.504
WHY?
BECAUSE I'M A WOMAN?

25:40.506 --> 25:42.006
IT WON'T HURT.

25:42.008 --> 25:44.675
LOOK, LAURA WASN'T ALLOWED
TO SPEAK IN COURT,

25:44.677 --> 25:47.811
SHE'S A VETERAN,
AND SHE KILLED HER OWN RAPIST.

25:47.813 --> 25:49.847
HOW MANY TIMES
DO YOU THINK I HAD TO GO OUT

25:49.849 --> 25:51.882
AND TALK ABOUT RACE
AND HOMICIDE?

25:51.884 --> 25:55.052
DON'T GET P.C. ON ME NOW.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.587
LET'S DO THINGS
IN THEIR PROPER ORDER, THEN,

25:56.589 --> 25:58.355
BECAUSE
FIRST WE'RE GONNA NEED

25:58.357 --> 26:00.424
TO GET CORPORAL DAY
A PUBLIC DEFENDER.

26:00.426 --> 26:02.493
YOU MIGHT WANT TO WAIT
ON ALL THIS.

26:02.495 --> 26:04.495
WHY?

26:04.497 --> 26:06.730
THE KNIFE WAS ON THE NEWS,
AND SHE WON'T SAY
HOW SHE USED IT.

26:06.732 --> 26:08.065
I HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH THAT.

26:08.067 --> 26:09.900
BASED ON WHAT --
YOUR INTUITION?

26:09.902 --> 26:12.536
SHE DESCRIBED THE APARTMENT,
THE PRIVACY FENCE,

26:12.538 --> 26:14.505
AND THE MUSIC TURNED UP
VERY LOUD.

26:14.507 --> 26:16.941
AS FOR ALL THESE OTHER DETAILS,
THE GIRL WAS DRUNK.

26:16.943 --> 26:18.275
YESTERDAY SHE TOLD ME

26:18.277 --> 26:20.578
LUCAS WAS MAKING GURGLING NOISES
AS HE DIED.

26:20.580 --> 26:22.446
SHE EVEN IMITATED
THE SOUND.

26:22.448 --> 26:24.181
NO WAY
SHE COULD HAVE HEARD THAT

26:24.183 --> 26:26.016
WITH THE STEREO BLASTING
AS LOUD AS IT WAS

26:26.018 --> 26:27.685
DURING THE STRUGGLE.

26:27.687 --> 26:31.255
SHE EITHER TURNED IT UP
AFTERWARDS, OR SHE'S LYING.

26:31.257 --> 26:32.523
SO, WHICH IS IT?

26:32.525 --> 26:35.759
QUIET ENOUGH
TO HEAR A DEATH RATTLE

26:35.761 --> 26:38.195
OR LOUD ENOUGH
TO WAKE UP THE NEIGHBORS?

26:38.197 --> 26:40.030
SHE CAN'T HAVE IT
BOTH WAYS.

26:40.032 --> 26:41.932
Taylor: I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

26:41.934 --> 26:43.434
WHY WOULD SHE KILL THE GUY,

26:43.436 --> 26:44.969
THEN LIE ABOUT
WHEN SHE TURNED UP THE MUSIC?

26:44.971 --> 26:48.305
THE MUSIC'S NOT WHAT
SHE'S LYING ABOUT, CHIEF.

26:48.307 --> 26:53.177
SHE'S LYING ABOUT
KILLING LUCAS CROSS.

26:54.813 --> 26:56.480
YEAH.

27:03.555 --> 27:05.923
THANK GOD I DON'T EVER
HAVE TO COME BACK HERE.

27:05.925 --> 27:07.124
LOOK, THIS IS THE SUITCASE
THEY GIVE ME.

27:07.126 --> 27:08.792
IS IT MADE OF CARDBOARD
OR SOMETHING?

27:08.794 --> 27:10.094
I GUESS
THE ONE GOOD THING IS

27:10.096 --> 27:11.729
I DON'T REALLY HAVE MUCH
TO PUT IN IT.

27:11.731 --> 27:13.831
OH, UM, DO YOU HAVE
MY PRESCRIPTION?

27:13.833 --> 27:16.266
I'LL JUST TOSS IT IN HERE
WITH MY CLOTHES.

27:16.268 --> 27:18.636
I COULDN'T FILL
YOUR PRESCRIPTION.

27:18.638 --> 27:20.404
WHAT?

27:22.173 --> 27:24.575
WHY?

27:24.577 --> 27:28.078
BECAUSE IT'S A FORGERY, MOM,
AND IT WASN'T GIVEN TO YOU HERE.
A FORGERY?

27:28.080 --> 27:30.347
WHAT ARE YOU --
IT'S NOT A FORGERY?

27:30.349 --> 27:34.084
LOOK, WE CAN --
NO ONE AT THIS REHAB
WOULD GIVE YOU THIS DRUG,

27:34.086 --> 27:36.687
AND YOU INVOLVED ME
IN A CRIME

27:36.689 --> 27:38.756
BY TRYING TO GET ME
TO FILL IT FOR YOU.
A CRIME?! OH, MY GOD!

27:38.758 --> 27:40.691
YES, MOM.
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

27:40.693 --> 27:44.662
DO I SEEM HIGH TO YOU
RIGHT NOW, RUSTY?

27:44.664 --> 27:45.996
LISTEN.

27:45.998 --> 27:49.833
I APOLOGIZED TO YOU,
OKAY?

27:49.835 --> 27:52.603
AND I MEANT
EVERY WORD OF IT.

27:52.605 --> 27:54.705
AND I'VE TRIED VERY HARD

27:54.707 --> 27:57.107
TO KEEP FROM MAKING THINGS
WORSE FOR YOU.

27:57.109 --> 28:01.679
BUT AS YOU SAID THE OTHER DAY,
YOU WERE NOT THE EASIEST KID.

28:01.681 --> 28:05.716
AND KNOWING WHAT YOU WERE,
HMM?

28:05.718 --> 28:08.118
EVEN WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE,
I KNEW WHAT YOU WERE.

28:08.120 --> 28:11.689
AND THAT HAS NEVER BEEN EASY
FOR ME, FACING THAT.

28:11.691 --> 28:14.692
[ SCOFFS ]
FACING WHAT?

28:14.694 --> 28:17.561
[ Chuckling ] OH, ARE YOU
PRETENDING THAT YOU'RE NOT GAY?

28:17.563 --> 28:20.831
BECAUSE I KNOW
THAT YOU ARE.

28:20.833 --> 28:24.001
AND [SCOFFS] I CAN OVERLOOK IT,
YOU KNOW?

28:24.003 --> 28:26.203
BUT CAN'T YOU JUST OVERLOOK
SOME OF MY PROBLEMS?

28:26.205 --> 28:29.740
AT LEAST I'M TRYING
TO BE NORMAL!

28:29.742 --> 28:32.042
I DON'T GET THAT HIT
OFF OF YOU.

28:32.044 --> 28:35.679
ARE YOU SAYING THAT YOU LET
YOUR BOYFRIEND BEAT ME UP

28:35.681 --> 28:38.248
AND YOU DUMPED ME OFF
AT THE ZOO...

28:38.250 --> 28:40.484
DUMPED YOU AT THE ZOO?
AND DROVE AWAY
AND GOT HIGH FOR THREE YEARS...

28:40.486 --> 28:42.753
I DIDN'T DUMP YOU
AT THE ZOO.
...BECAUSE YOU KNEW
I WAS GAY, MOM?

28:42.755 --> 28:44.555
GARY WOULDN'T LET ME
COME BACK AND GET YOU!
YES, YOU DID!

28:44.557 --> 28:46.824
AND THEN THEY PUT YOU
IN A FOSTER HOME.

28:46.826 --> 28:49.093
WHERE I WAS
KNOCKED AROUND, MOM.
YEAH, AND THEN YOU CHOSE
TO GO OUT ON THE STREET

28:49.095 --> 28:52.229
AND DO THOSE THINGS
FOR MONEY WITH GUYS!

28:52.231 --> 28:55.065
AND WHERE DO YOU THINK
I LEARNED HOW TO DO THAT, MOM?

28:55.067 --> 28:57.067
OR --
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

28:57.069 --> 28:58.669
I'M NOT BLAMING YOU,
RUSTY.

28:58.671 --> 29:02.906
OKAY? AND I'M ASSUMING
YOU DID THE BEST THAT YOU COULD

29:02.908 --> 29:05.776
AND THAT
YOU CAN'T HELP YOURSELF.

29:07.412 --> 29:10.347
I THINK I SHOULD GO.
WHAT? NO. COME ON.

29:10.349 --> 29:13.684
CAN'T YOU JUST SHOW ME
SOME OF THE FORGIVENESS
THAT I AM SHOWING YOU?

29:13.686 --> 29:16.086
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF
THE OTHER DAY --

29:16.088 --> 29:18.455
YOU WERE NOT AN EASY CHILD.

29:18.457 --> 29:20.924
AND I REALLY DID.
I TRIED TO HELP YOU.

29:20.926 --> 29:23.527
I REALLY -- I DID TRY.

29:23.529 --> 29:25.462
ALL RIGHT.
I APOLOGIZE, TOO.

29:25.464 --> 29:27.798
I AM SORRY FOR BEING
SUCH A DIFFICULT KID

29:27.800 --> 29:29.600
THAT IT FORCED YOU
TO DO DRUGS.

29:29.602 --> 29:32.402
I AM SORRY FOR NOT BEING THE
NORMAL CHILD THAT YOU DESERVE.

29:32.404 --> 29:34.271
AND, YOU KNOW, MAYBE
IF YOU DIDN'T SEE ME AGAIN,

29:34.273 --> 29:36.306
YOU'LL GET BETTER.

29:36.308 --> 29:38.475
WHY DON'T WE TRY THAT?

29:38.477 --> 29:40.477
WAIT. WAIT!
WAIT ONE SECOND.

29:40.479 --> 29:42.980
RUSTY,
I GET PAST YOU BEING GAY

29:42.982 --> 29:44.815
AND ALL THE TROUBLE
THAT THAT CAUSED ME,

29:44.817 --> 29:46.617
AND YOUR RESPONSE IS
TO JUST WALK AWAY?

29:46.619 --> 29:48.619
♪ I'VE WATCHED YOU CHANGE

29:48.621 --> 29:50.387
YOU THINK
THAT SOMEHOW I'M WORSE

29:50.389 --> 29:53.991
THAN A GAY BOY
WHO SOLD HIMSELF ON THE STREET?

29:53.993 --> 29:55.626
I FORGAVE YOU.

29:55.628 --> 29:58.228
AND YOU ARE NOT BIG ENOUGH
TO FORGIVE ME.

29:58.230 --> 30:01.899
♪ I LOOKED AWAY

30:01.901 --> 30:04.301
WAIT. RUSTY,
I'LL PAY YOU BACK.

30:04.303 --> 30:06.403
LOOK, I PROMISED
THAT I WOULD PAY YOU BACK.

30:06.405 --> 30:08.138
WOULD YOU LISTEN TO ME?
RUSTY. RUSTY!

30:08.140 --> 30:11.441
IF YOU WALK OUT THAT DOOR
AND LEAVE ME LIKE THIS...

30:11.443 --> 30:15.179
♪ I WATCHED A CHANGE
...I WILL
NEVER FORGIVE YOU!

30:15.181 --> 30:17.948
♪ IN YOU
I WILL
NEVER FORGIVE YOU!

30:17.950 --> 30:20.350
♪ IT'S LIKE YOU NEVER

30:20.352 --> 30:22.452
THE MUSIC WAS REALLY LOUD,
LIEUTENANT.

30:22.454 --> 30:24.688
YEAH, I REMEMBER,
AND IT'S STILL REALLY LOUD.

30:24.690 --> 30:27.825
FOR THE LOVE OF GOD,
WHY IS THIS IMPORTANT?
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

30:27.827 --> 30:30.661
NEIGHBOR CALLED IN THE NOISE
COMPLAINT AT 9:35 P.M.

30:30.663 --> 30:33.330
AND THEN ANNOUNCED IT
TO THE WORLD ON THE 11:00 NEWS.

30:33.332 --> 30:34.832
NOW WATCH ALL THIS.

30:34.834 --> 30:37.000
<i>THE MUSIC WAS SO LOUD,</i>
<i>I CALLED 911.</i>

30:37.002 --> 30:39.203
<i>AND WE DON'T KNOW</i>
<i>IF THE STABBING OF MR. CROSS</i>

30:39.205 --> 30:42.105
<i>WAS A PREMEDITATED ACT OF</i>
<i>MURDER OR DONE IN SELF-DEFENSE.</i>

30:42.107 --> 30:44.374
<i>ALL I CAN SAY</i>
<i>WITH ANY CERTAINTY AT THIS TIME</i>

30:44.376 --> 30:46.176
<i>WAS THE VICTIM</i>
<i>WAS TRIED FOR RAPE</i>

30:46.178 --> 30:48.345
<i>AND HIS CASE WAS DISMISSED.</i>

30:48.347 --> 30:50.047
WELL, TIP OF THE HAT
TO DDA LEE

30:50.049 --> 30:52.616
FOR GIVING AWAY THE PERTINENT
FACTS OF THE MURDER.

30:52.618 --> 30:55.319
THAT'S ALL LAURA HAD TO HEAR
TO INVENT HER CONFESSION.

30:55.321 --> 30:57.521
NOBODY STOPS
IN THE MIDDLE OF A KNIFE FIGHT

30:57.523 --> 30:59.056
TO TURN ON THE SOUND SYSTEM,
SIR.

30:59.058 --> 31:00.824
AND WHY WOULD YOU TURN IT UP
SO LOUD

31:00.826 --> 31:02.626
RIGHT BEFORE
YOU WERE READY TO LEAVE?

31:02.628 --> 31:05.028
WELL, HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT
IT HAPPENED AFTER THE MURDER?

31:05.030 --> 31:08.065
WE FOUND A BLOODY GLOVE PRINT
ON THE VOLUME CONTROL.

31:08.067 --> 31:09.466
OH.

31:09.468 --> 31:11.034
THE BLOOD. WELL...

31:11.036 --> 31:12.870
Sykes: THE KILLER
TURNED IT UP LOUD ENOUGH

31:12.872 --> 31:14.037
FOR THE POLICE TO BE CALLED.

31:14.039 --> 31:15.539
AND WHY WOULD SHE DO THAT?

31:15.541 --> 31:17.574
TO ESTABLISH
THE TIME OF DEATH.

31:17.576 --> 31:20.244
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO BACK OVER

31:20.246 --> 31:23.213
OUR FIRST SUSPECT'S
ALIBI DINNER IN MALIBU.

31:23.215 --> 31:25.916
I'M GONNA BRING THE CAPTAIN
UP TO DATE.

31:25.918 --> 31:28.252
[ DOOR OPENS ]

31:28.254 --> 31:32.055
SHE CHECKED HER CAR
WITH THE VALET AT 8:27 P.M.

31:32.057 --> 31:34.258
SHE EVEN KEPT THE PARKING STUB
TO PROVE IT.

31:34.260 --> 31:36.426
PAID HER BILL
WITH A CREDIT CARD AT 10:53.

31:36.428 --> 31:38.562
MA'AM, WE CHASED DOWN
A HARD COPY OF THE RECEIPT

31:38.564 --> 31:40.230
FROM THE CORAL RIDGE GRILL

31:40.232 --> 31:42.833
AND COMPARED IT TO THE STATEMENT
THAT SHE SIGNED FOR US.

31:42.835 --> 31:44.501
NOT HER SIGNATURE.

31:44.503 --> 31:46.503
IF MISS CHAIDEZ
WENT TO ALL THIS TROUBLE

31:46.505 --> 31:47.905
CREATING THE PERFECT ALIBI,

31:47.907 --> 31:49.406
IS THERE ANY CHANCE

31:49.408 --> 31:51.441
SHE WAS WORKING
WITH CORPORAL DAY?

31:51.443 --> 31:54.344
WELL, WE KNOW WHOEVER SIGNED
THE CREDIT CARD BILL

31:54.346 --> 31:56.413
SAT AT TABLE NUMBER 17.

31:56.415 --> 31:58.048
HOLD ON.
WE'RE FINDING TABLE NUMBER 17

31:58.050 --> 31:59.750
THE NIGHT OF THE MURDER
RIGHT NOW.

31:59.752 --> 32:02.519
Buzz: WE'VE BEEN CHECKING
FACEBOOK AND INSTAGRAM POSTINGS

32:02.521 --> 32:04.187
MARKED #CORALRIDGEGRILL.

32:04.189 --> 32:06.790
NOW, THIS IS NOT
TABLE NUMBER 17.

32:06.792 --> 32:08.458
THIS WAS A BUNCH OF GUYS
FROM LOUISIANA

32:08.460 --> 32:09.960
AT TABLE NUMBER 9, BUT...

32:09.962 --> 32:12.529
BEHIND THEM AND TO THE RIGHT
IS TABLE NUMBER 17.

32:12.531 --> 32:14.631
THE PICTURE WAS TAKEN
AT 9:44 P.M.

32:14.633 --> 32:17.134
NOW, IF WE ENLARGE IT...

32:17.136 --> 32:21.271
THE PERSON SEATED AT TABLE
NUMBER 17 IS NOT JACKIE.

32:21.273 --> 32:23.340
LOOKS JUST LIKE HER.
WHO IS IT?

32:24.976 --> 32:27.878
Tao: WE FOUND BLOOD
IN YOUR SISTER'S CAR.

32:27.880 --> 32:30.614
THAT BLOOD WILL MATCH UP
WITH LUCAS CROSS.

32:30.616 --> 32:34.618
WE ALSO FOUND SHARDS OF GLASS
IN HER FLOOR MAT

32:34.620 --> 32:37.921
FROM THE BROKEN WINE BOTTLE.

32:37.923 --> 32:39.589
[ SIGHS ]

32:39.591 --> 32:43.327
MY LITTLE SISTER HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH ANYTHING.

32:43.329 --> 32:45.228
Sharon:
THAT'S A SHAME...

32:45.230 --> 32:49.132
BECAUSE HER CAR
WAS VERY ACTIVE IN THIS CRIME.

32:49.134 --> 32:52.302
HARD TO BELIEVE
SHE EXCHANGED VEHICLES WITH YOU

32:52.304 --> 32:54.137
THE NIGHT OF THE MURDER
WITHOUT KNOWING WHY.

32:54.139 --> 32:57.007
THAT IS
ACCESSORY TO MURDER.

32:57.009 --> 32:59.910
AND I'D FEEL FINE
ARRESTING HER FOR THAT.

32:59.912 --> 33:01.645
<i>RIGHT NOW.</i>

33:01.647 --> 33:03.246
OH, YOU ALREADY HAVE ONE WOMAN
CONFESSING TO THIS MURDER.

33:03.248 --> 33:04.648
CORPORAL DAY WAS LYING.

33:04.650 --> 33:06.650
THAT'S GONNA BE VERY HARD
TO EXPLAIN.

33:06.652 --> 33:08.986
LUCKILY, WE'RE IN
THE EXPLANATION BUSINESS.

33:08.988 --> 33:10.320
WHAT BUSINESS ARE YOU IN?

33:10.322 --> 33:11.655
Jackie: [ <i>SNIFFLES</i> ]

33:11.657 --> 33:13.824
OH, GOD.

33:13.826 --> 33:15.692
I ASKED CATHY
TO SWITCH CARS.

33:15.694 --> 33:18.161
I MADE THE RESERVATION
AT THE RESTAURANT.

33:18.163 --> 33:19.830
I GAVE HER MY CREDIT CARD,

33:19.832 --> 33:21.331
AND I TOLD HER I WAS
TREATING HER TO DINNER.

33:21.333 --> 33:22.799
SHE DIDN'T ASK WHY,
AND I DIDN'T TELL HER.

33:22.801 --> 33:24.868
SHE HAD NO IDEA
WHAT I WAS GOING TO DO.

33:27.638 --> 33:29.206
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

33:29.208 --> 33:32.009
BUT MAYBE YOUR SISTER
CAN EXPLAIN THAT TO A JURY

33:32.011 --> 33:35.679
AND SEE HOW
12 RATIONAL PEOPLE REACT.

33:35.681 --> 33:37.214
I DON'T LIKE HER CHANCES.

33:37.216 --> 33:38.882
OH, MY GOD.

33:38.884 --> 33:41.385
OH, MY GOD. NO.

33:41.387 --> 33:43.353
<i>HE SENT ME FLOWERS</i>
<i>AFTER THE TRIAL.</i>

33:43.355 --> 33:46.523
HE WAS STANDING IN LINE
BEHIND ME AT STARBUCKS.
THIS WAS SELF-DEFENSE.

33:46.525 --> 33:49.026
NOT UNLESS THERE WAS
AN IMMEDIATE THREAT TO YOUR LIFE

33:49.028 --> 33:50.460
AND YOU HAD
NO OTHER ALTERNATIVE.

33:50.462 --> 33:52.896
BUT THAT'S NOT
WHAT HAPPENED.

33:52.898 --> 33:55.032
YOU CALLED LUCAS BACK,
DIDN'T YOU?

33:55.034 --> 33:58.001
AND YOU ACTED LIKE
YOU WANTED TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

33:58.003 --> 34:00.737
YOU DROVE TO HIS APARTMENT
IN YOUR SISTER'S CAR.

34:00.739 --> 34:03.240
YOU WAITED UNTIL
HE TURNED HIS BACK ON YOU

34:03.242 --> 34:05.142
TO GET A BOTTLE OF WINE.

34:05.144 --> 34:07.978
YOU REACHED INTO YOUR PURSE.

34:07.980 --> 34:09.346
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

34:09.348 --> 34:10.881
AND THEN
WHEN YOU HAD A CHANCE,

34:10.883 --> 34:13.316
YOU GAVE HIM
A PEPPER SPRAY.
UGH!

34:13.318 --> 34:15.419
HE DROPPED
THE WINE BOTTLE...
OH, GOD!

34:15.421 --> 34:16.920
...WENT TO COVER HIS EYES.

34:16.922 --> 34:19.389
[ GRUNTS ]
UGH!

34:19.391 --> 34:20.991
THEN YOU STABBED HIM
IN THE BACK,

34:20.993 --> 34:24.428
GRABBED HIM BY THE HAIR,
AND YOU SLIT HIS THROAT.

34:26.831 --> 34:30.567
THEN YOU PICKED UP THE WINE
BOTTLE AND SMASHED HIS FACE IN.

34:30.569 --> 34:32.502
[ GRUNTS ]
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

34:32.504 --> 34:35.238
AND WHEN YOU WERE SURE
HE WAS DEAD,

34:35.240 --> 34:37.207
YOU TURNED UP THE MUSIC...
[ DEFTONES' "CHANGE (IN
THE HOUSE OF FLIES)" PLAYS ]

34:37.209 --> 34:39.242
...WASHED THE BLOOD
OFF YOUR HANDS IN THE SINK,

34:39.244 --> 34:41.912
GOT RID OF YOUR CLOTHES.

34:41.914 --> 34:46.583
AND I SLEPT THROUGH THE NIGHT
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MONTHS.

34:46.585 --> 34:48.652
MM.

34:49.854 --> 34:51.288
GOOD FOR YOU.

34:51.290 --> 34:52.622
SATISFIED, LEE?

34:52.624 --> 34:54.624
[ SIGHS ]

34:54.626 --> 34:56.426
GO AHEAD.

34:56.428 --> 34:59.930
ARREST HER FOR MURDER
AND SEE IF A JURY WILL CONVICT.

34:59.932 --> 35:04.468
THAT'S YOUR SOLUTION
AS A SWORN OFFICER OF THE COURT?

35:04.470 --> 35:06.770
Flynn: SO, WHAT
ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO --

35:06.772 --> 35:09.439
JUST SIT BACK AND LET VIGILANTES
DO FOR US WHAT WE CAN'T?

35:09.441 --> 35:12.709
YOU GAVE AWAY
THE MURDER WEAPON ON TV.

35:12.711 --> 35:14.311
THAT ALSO DOESN'T HELP.

35:14.313 --> 35:15.979
WELL, NEITHER DOES
YOUR OTHER SUSPECT --

35:15.981 --> 35:17.814
CORPORAL DAY.

35:17.816 --> 35:21.318
YOU REMEMBER HER --
THE WOMAN WHO CONFESSED TWICE.

35:21.320 --> 35:23.386
AND WHAT KIND OF DEAL
IS OUR OFFICE SUPPOSED TO MAKE

35:23.388 --> 35:24.788
WHILE ANOTHER CREDIBLE SUSPECT
IS OUT THERE

35:24.790 --> 35:26.456
TAKING CREDIT
FOR THE CRIME?

35:26.458 --> 35:28.558
WELL, YOU WON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT IT, NOW, WILL YOU, LEE,

35:28.560 --> 35:31.495
BECAUSE YOU WON'T BE MAKING
ANY DEALS.

35:31.497 --> 35:33.630
Sharon: <i>WAS LAURA DAY</i>
<i>INVOLVED IN THIS?</i>

35:33.632 --> 35:35.398
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

35:35.400 --> 35:37.167
<i>I NEVER EVEN MET HER.</i>

35:37.169 --> 35:38.568
[ SCOFFS ]

35:38.570 --> 35:40.604
I KNEW
CORPORAL DAY DIDN'T DO IT.

35:40.606 --> 35:41.972
I KNEW IT.

35:41.974 --> 35:45.509
WELL, DON'T HIGH-FIVE YOURSELF
TOO HARD.

35:45.511 --> 35:48.478
DDA LEE
IS RIGHT ABOUT ONE THING --

35:48.480 --> 35:51.815
WE NEED TO GET LAURA
TO WITHDRAW THAT CONFESSION,

35:51.817 --> 35:54.217
OR THIS CASE WILL NEVER MAKE.

36:02.293 --> 36:04.361
CLEAR SOMETHING UP FOR ME,
CORPORAL.

36:04.363 --> 36:05.829
WHAT WAS
YOUR BEST-CASE SCENARIO?

36:05.831 --> 36:07.931
LIFE BEHIND BARS
FOR A CRIME YOU DIDN'T COMMIT?

36:07.933 --> 36:09.366
I'M ALREADY DOING LIFE.

36:09.368 --> 36:11.835
I MIGHT AS WELL ACCOMPLISH
SOME GOOD FOR THE WORLD

36:11.837 --> 36:12.802
WHILE I'M AT IT.

36:12.804 --> 36:14.838
JACKIE IS A HERO,

36:14.840 --> 36:17.707
AND HEROES DESERVE
TO BE REWARDED, NOT PUNISHED.

36:17.709 --> 36:20.277
MY CONFESSION
WILL MONKEY-WRENCH HER CASE

36:20.279 --> 36:21.678
WHEN IT GOES TO TRIAL.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.380
LOOK [SIGHS]

36:23.382 --> 36:25.615
YOU'RE GOING TO EXTREME LENGTHS
TO HELP SOMEONE ELSE.

36:25.617 --> 36:27.717
WHY DON'T YOU HELP YOURSELF
A LITTLE, TOO?

36:27.719 --> 36:31.454
I HAVE TRIED HELPING MYSELF.
I HAVE.

36:31.456 --> 36:32.956
I HAVE BEEN TO THE V.A.

36:32.958 --> 36:35.725
I'VE SEEN THE SHRINKS.
I'VE TAKEN THE PILLS.

36:35.727 --> 36:38.662
NOTHING WORKS. NOTHING.

36:38.664 --> 36:41.731
LYING ABOUT KILLING LUCAS
WON'T FIX IT, EITHER.

36:43.701 --> 36:46.036
GIVE YOUR STATEMENT
ONE LAST TIME.

36:46.038 --> 36:50.407
LET JACKIE PLEAD GUILTY
TO SOMETHING LESS THAN MURDER.

36:50.409 --> 36:54.211
AND THAT IS
WHAT YOU CALL FAIR?

36:54.213 --> 36:57.948
IT'S NOT CALLED
THE FAIRNESS SYSTEM.

36:59.884 --> 37:02.052
JUST TELL ME
THIS ONE THING.

37:02.054 --> 37:04.721
THE KNIFE WAS IN THE NEWS,

37:04.723 --> 37:08.258
BUT NO ONE KNEW
LUCAS HAD HIS THROAT CUT.

37:08.260 --> 37:13.563
SO, WHEN YOU TOLD ME THAT,
WAS -- WAS IT A LUCKY GUESS?

37:13.565 --> 37:16.099
A LUCKY GUESS?

37:16.101 --> 37:17.667
ARE YOU KIDDING?

37:17.669 --> 37:21.571
DIDN'T YOU TRAIN
WITH WEAPONS AT ALL?

37:21.573 --> 37:23.573
OR WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE DONE,
SOLDIER?

37:23.575 --> 37:28.912
ONLY ONE WAY TO TAKE DOWN
A GUY THAT BIG IN CLOSE QUARTERS

37:28.914 --> 37:31.147
BEFORE HE CRUSHES YOU.

37:32.516 --> 37:34.851
YOU CUT HIS THROAT.

37:36.587 --> 37:41.291
I USED TO PRETEND
THAT I WOULD CUT HIS THROAT

37:41.293 --> 37:44.427
THREE AND FOUR TIMES
A DAY.

37:44.429 --> 37:46.763
BUT I DIDN'T HAVE
THE GUTS.

37:46.765 --> 37:49.799
[ Voice breaking ]
AND NOW SOMEBODY ELSE
HAS DONE IT FOR ME,

37:49.801 --> 37:53.303
AND I WILL NEVER KNOW
IF IT WOULD HAVE HELPED.

37:53.305 --> 37:57.907
OH, MY GOD,
I WILL NEVER KNOW.

37:57.909 --> 38:00.043
[ Sobbing ]
I WILL NEVER KNOW.

38:00.045 --> 38:03.546
I WILL NEVER KNOW.

38:03.548 --> 38:06.549
I WILL NEVER KNOW.

38:06.551 --> 38:09.452
OKAY.

38:09.454 --> 38:11.087
[ SOBBING ]

38:11.089 --> 38:16.159
HE'S GONE TO WHERE
HE CAN NEVER HURT ANYONE AGAIN.

38:16.161 --> 38:19.229
NOW LET'S HELP THE WOMAN
THAT PUT HIM THERE, OKAY?

38:19.231 --> 38:20.764
WHY AM I CRYING?

38:20.766 --> 38:23.800
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I'M CRYING.

38:23.802 --> 38:25.135
[ SNIFFLING ]

38:25.137 --> 38:27.003
OKAY, JUST --
JUST HELP ME STOP CRYING,

38:27.005 --> 38:29.839
AND I'LL TELL THE TRUTH.

38:29.841 --> 38:34.811
JUST HELP ME.
JUST HELP ME STOP CRYING.

38:34.813 --> 38:36.646
OKAY.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.848
[ SOBBING ]

38:45.156 --> 38:48.258
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

38:48.260 --> 38:50.760
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

39:03.874 --> 39:05.942
HELLO?

39:05.944 --> 39:08.511
HONEY, DON'T --
DON'T HANG UP, OKAY?
[ HORNS HONKING ]

39:08.513 --> 39:10.280
LISTEN,
I WAS STUPID AND WRONG,

39:10.282 --> 39:11.881
AND I DIDN'T MEAN ANY OF
THE THINGS THAT I SAID EARLIER.

39:11.883 --> 39:13.950
And I am so --
I'm so, so sorry.

39:13.952 --> 39:15.552
OKAY.

39:15.554 --> 39:18.955
AND, UM, YOU KNOW I'LL ALWAYS
LOVE YOU, RIGHT, HONEY?

39:18.957 --> 39:21.858
[ CAN CLATTERS ]
Always.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.393
YEAH. I KNOW.

39:23.395 --> 39:26.296
HONEY, LOOK, UM...

39:26.298 --> 39:28.365
[ Chuckling ]
I NEED A RIDE.

39:28.367 --> 39:30.667
UM, SARAH WAS SUPPOSED
TO PICK ME UP,

39:30.669 --> 39:32.502
BUT GOD KNOWS
WHERE THE HELL SHE IS.

39:32.504 --> 39:33.837
WAIT. WAIT. WAIT. WAIT.

39:33.839 --> 39:35.905
SARAH WAS SUPPOSED
TO PICK YOU UP?

39:35.907 --> 39:37.207
I THOUGHT SIGNAL HILL

39:37.209 --> 39:38.842
WAS DRIVING YOU
TO THE HALFWAY HOUSE.

39:38.844 --> 39:40.243
Who is Sarah?

39:40.245 --> 39:41.578
[ SIGHS ]

39:43.080 --> 39:44.714
IT'S 11:30 P.M., MOM.

39:44.716 --> 39:47.217
THE ONLY REASON I AM UP THIS
LATE IS BECAUSE I AM STUDYING,

39:47.219 --> 39:48.351
AND I CAN'T HELP YOU.

39:48.353 --> 39:49.652
BUT -- BUT I'M STRANDED.

39:49.654 --> 39:51.755
I AM STRANDED BY --
THERE'S --

39:51.757 --> 39:53.890
THERE'S LIKE A TACO PLACE AND --
I DON'T KNOW.

39:53.892 --> 39:56.259
IT'S LIKE A PARKING LOT
OR SOMETHING.

39:56.261 --> 39:58.161
Listen, honey, okay?

39:58.163 --> 40:00.430
I DIDN'T MAKE IT
TO THE HALFWAY HOUSE

40:00.432 --> 40:02.499
and I just need to go there

40:02.501 --> 40:04.934
AND I NEED TO SEE THAT
THEY'RE STILL GONNA LET ME IN.

40:04.936 --> 40:10.173
SO [SNIFFLES] IF YOU COULD JUST
COME AND GET ME, RUSTY,

40:10.175 --> 40:13.276
I WILL NEVER -- I WILL NEVER
ASK YOU FOR ANYTHING

40:13.278 --> 40:15.345
EVER, EVER AGAIN, OKAY?

40:15.347 --> 40:19.115
BUT, LIKE, THIS IS, LIKE,
NOT A NICE PART OF TOWN.

40:19.117 --> 40:21.951
YOU GOT OUT OF REHAB
LAST NIGHT,

40:21.953 --> 40:24.587
AND YOU ARE
ALREADY DRINKING?

40:24.589 --> 40:26.189
THREE BEERS
IS NOT DRINKING!

40:26.191 --> 40:27.857
And you know what?

40:27.859 --> 40:30.693
I needed that much
to get over our little fight.

40:30.695 --> 40:32.629
IT WAS NOT A LITTLE FIGHT.

40:32.631 --> 40:36.633
It was -- It was a big, terrible
bunch of lies that you told me.

40:36.635 --> 40:40.437
I AM NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR YOUR DRINKING,

40:40.439 --> 40:43.540
and I am not driving you
to the halfway house.

40:43.542 --> 40:46.342
GO BACK TO REHAB
AND START OVER. GOODBYE.

40:49.647 --> 40:53.149
[ RECEIVER CLICKING ]

40:53.151 --> 40:55.785
[ EXHALES HEAVILY ]

40:55.787 --> 40:59.055
I'M SO SORRY.

40:59.057 --> 41:02.992
THAT THIS HAPPENED
OR THAT SHE'LL ONLY CALL BACK?

41:02.994 --> 41:05.829
IT SOUNDS LIKE HER ON THE PHONE,
I KNOW,

41:05.831 --> 41:08.965
BUT IT'S HER ADDICTION TALKING,
NOT YOUR MOM.

41:08.967 --> 41:13.169
WHY DO I EVEN CARE
ANYMORE?

41:13.171 --> 41:14.804
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]
BECAUSE YOU LOVE HER

41:14.806 --> 41:18.141
AND BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
TO GIVE UP HOPE

41:18.143 --> 41:20.677
THAT SOMEDAY
SHE'LL BE WELL.

41:24.582 --> 41:26.549
BUT NOT TONIGHT.
